  • public class ORedConditionsType
extends BaseConditionsType
    A list of boolean comparisons, or boolean groups that are logically ORed together. Any ANDed conditions in the list are evaluated first.

    Java class for ORedConditionsType complex type.

      • getConditionOrANDedConditionsOrTypeCondition

        public java.util.List<BaseConditionsType> getConditionOrANDedConditionsOrTypeCondition()
        Gets the value of the conditionOrANDedConditionsOrTypeCondition property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the conditionOrANDedConditionsOrTypeCondition property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getConditionOrANDedConditionsOrTypeCondition().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list ComparisonType ANDedConditionsType TypeCheckType
